<!-- Game Description Table -->

<table class="tablestyle" id="table14" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="sectional">

<!-- Game Description Header -->
		
		<table class="headertable" id="table15" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td class="headercell">
				<img border="0" src="../../../images/headers/gamedes.jpg" width="240" height="33"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>Wrestling is a martial art[citation needed] that uses grappling type techniques such as clinch fighting, throws and takedowns, joint locks, pins and other grappling holds. A wrestling bout is a physical competition, between two (occasionally more) competitors or sparring partners, who attempt to gain and maintain a superior position. There are a wide range of styles with varying rules with both traditional historic and modern styles. Wrestling techniques have been incorporated into other martial arts as well as military hand-to-hand combat systems.
                  <br><br>Japanese professional wrestling, also known as puroresu, is treated as a sport rather than the entertainment style of wrestling found in North America. There are no storylines or any sort of angle found in most puroresu promotions. The matches have the atmosphere of real wrestling competition. Techniques include use of amateur or shoot wrestling tactics in addition to hard hitting martial arts strikes and complex submission maneuvers. This means that the wrestlers are more prone to injury. Popular Japanese wrestlers include Kenta Kobashi, Tiger Mask, The Great Muta, Jun Akiyama, Jushin "Thunder" Liger, and KENTA.
                  <br><br>New Japan Pro-Wrestling is a major professional wrestling promotion in Japan and is a member of the National Wrestling Alliance[citation needed], founded by Antonio Inoki in 1972. Owing to its TV program aired on TV Asahi, it is the largest wrestling promotion in Japan and one of the largest in the world.
                  <br><br>Shin Nihon Pro Wrestling - Toukon Retsuden 3 is the third and last sequel for the Playstation One console to one of the most popular wrestling games ever made. The game still maintained its wonderful polygon graphics, large range of moves, and smooth game control.
                  <br><br>The new game has all of the old favorite wrestlers, plus new wrestlers like Chris Benoit, Tiger Mask, and Antonio Inoki. Tag Team and Battle Royal modes have also been added. New moves, arenas, and new situation moves (like running tackles) have added to the game.
                  <br><br>Wrestlers:
                  <br>- Antonio Inoki
                  <br>- Tatsumi Fujinami
                  <br>- Riki Choshu
                  <br>- Shinya Hashimoto
                  <br>- Kensuke Sasaki
                  <br>- Osamu Kido
                  <br>- Junji Hirata
                  <br>- Osamu Nishimura
                  <br>- Satoshi Kojima
                  <br>- Manabu Nakanishi
                  <br>- Taduo Yasuda
                  <br>- Jyushin "Thunder" Lyger
                  <br>- El Samurai
                  <br>- Wild Pegasus
                  <br>- Chris Benoit
                  <br>- Black Tiger Eddy Guerrero
                  <br>- Kendo Ka Shin
                  <br>- Koji Kanemoto
                  <br>- Shinjiro Ohtani
                  <br>- Tastuhito Takaiwa
                  <br>- Power Warrior
                  <br>- Rick Steiner
                  <br>- Scott Steiner
                  <br>- Young Antonio Inoki
                  <br>- Seiji Sakagutchi
                  <br>- Young (Battle) Lyger
                  <br>- Super Strong Machine
                  <br>- Young (Babyface) Chono
                  <br>- Unmasked Lyger
                  <br>- Masahiro Chono
                  <br>- Keiji Mutoh
                  <br>- The Great Muta
                  <br>- Scott Norton
                  <br>- Hiroyoshi Tenzan
                  <br>- Shiro Koshinaka
                  <br>- Kengo Kimura
                  <br>- Yoshiaki Fujiwara
                  <br>- The Great Sasuke
                  <br>- Super Delfin
                  <br>- Jinsei Shinzaki
                  <br>- Naoya Ogawa
                  <br>- Kazuo Yamazaki
                  <br>- Tiger King
                  <br>- Tiger Mask
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>Fighting spirit of the original Porigonpuroresu Retsuden ?[third series. Production and improved graphics and more realistic! Other organizations, including players, 39 appeared. Edit mode is also possible to create a new wrestler with the original. Warm the hearts of wrestling fans to the game mode, expand the range of play! !
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>Third person perspective.</li>
			<li>3D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Japanese Wrestling theme.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

